  "body": "This allows code like `vec![1i, 2, 3].len();` to work.\n\nThis breaks code that uses macros as statements without putting\nsemicolons after them, such as:\n\n```\nfn main() {\n    ...\n    assert!(a == b)\n    assert!(c == d)\n    println(...);\n}\n```\n\nIt also breaks code that uses macros as items without semicolons:\n\n```\nfn main() {\n    local_data_key!(foo)\n\n    println(\"hello world\")\n}\n```\n\nAdd semicolons to fix this code. Those two examples can be fixed as\nfollows:\n\n```\nfn main() {\n    ...\n    assert!(a == b);\n    assert!(c == d);\n    println(...);\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    local_data_key!(foo);\n\n    println(\"hello world\")\n}\n```\n\nRFC #378.\n\nCloses #18635.\n\n[breaking-change]\n\nr? @alexcrichton \n",
